    'pool_item_pump_summary'                    => 'In summary, a pool pump is essential for maintaining clean and safe water in a swimming pool, as well as ensuring the longevity and efficiency of the pool equipment.',
    'pool_item_filter_title'                    => 'Filter',
    'pool_item_filter_desc_1'                   => 'The primary function of a pool filter is to remove contaminants, debris, and other particles from the water in a swimming pool. Without a pool filter, the water would quickly become cloudy, dirty, and potentially harmful to swimmers. A properly functioning pool filter helps to maintain clear, clean, and healthy water.',
    'pool_item_filter_desc_2'                   => 'A clean and well-maintained pool filter is also essential for ensuring the health and safety of swimmers. Without a filter, harmful bacteria and other microorganisms can thrive in the pool water, leading to illnesses and infections. A pool filter helps to remove these contaminants, making the water safe for swimming.',
    'pool_item_filter_desc_3'                   => 'A pool filter also helps to protect other pool equipment, such as pumps, heaters, and pool surfaces, by removing particles that can cause damage or clog the equipment. This can extend the lifespan of pool equipment and reduce maintenance and repair costs over time.',
    'pool_item_filter_summary'                  => 'In summary, a pool filter helps to maintain clean and clear water, ensures the health and safety of swimmers, and protects other pool equipment. Regular maintenance and cleaning of the pool filter are important to ensure that it operates effectively and efficiently.',
    'pool_item_clean_accs_title'                => 'Cleaning Accessories',
    'pool_item_clean_accs_body'                 => 'There are several accessories that are commonly used for the maintenance of a swimming pool. These are the ones we use regularly on all pools.',
    'pool_item_skimmer_title'                   => 'Pool Skimmer',
    'pool_item_skimmer_body'                    => 'A pool skimmer is a net-like device that is used to remove debris, leaves, and other floating particles from the surface of the water. The skimmer is attached to a telescoping pole that can be adjusted to reach different areas of the pool.',
    'pool_item_brush_title'                     => 'Pool Brush',
    'pool_item_brush_body'                      => 'A pool brush is used to scrub the walls, floor, and steps of the pool to remove dirt, algae, and other stubborn stains. The brush is typically attached to a telescoping pole for ease of use.',
    'pool_item_vacuum_title'                    => 'Pool Vacuum',
    'pool_item_vacuum_body'                     => 'A pool vacuum is used to clean the pool floor and walls of debris and other particles. There are several types of pool vacuums available, including manual, automatic, and robotic models.',
    'pool_item_test_kit_title'                  => 'Pool Test Kit',
    'pool_item_test_kit_body'                   => 'A pool test kit is used to measure the chemical levels of the pool water, including pH, chlorine, alkalinity, and hardness. Maintaining proper chemical balance is essential for maintaining a healthy and safe swimming environment.',
    'pool_item_chemicals_title'                 => 'Pool Chemicals',
    'pool_item_chemicals_body'                  => 'Pool chemicals are used to maintain proper water chemistry and ensure a clean and safe swimming environment. These are some of the pool chemicals we use regularly.',
    'pool_item_chlorine_title'                  => 'Chlorine',
    'pool_item_chlorine_body'                   => 'Chlorine is a sanitizer that is used to kill bacteria, viruses, and other harmful microorganisms in the pool water. It comes in different forms, including tablets, granules, and liquid. Chlorine is the most commonly used pool chemical and is essential for maintaining a safe and healthy swimming environment.',
    'pool_item_ph_adjuster_title'               => 'pH Adjusters',
    'pool_item_ph_adjuster_body'                => 'The pH level of the pool water should be between 7.2 and 7.8 for optimal swimming conditions. pH adjusters, such as sodium carbonate and hydrochloric acid, are used to raise or lower the pH level as needed.',
    'pool_item_alkalinity_title'                => 'Alkalinity Adjusters',
    'pool_item_alkalinity_body'                 => 'Alkalinity is a measure of the pool water\'s ability to resist changes in pH. Alkalinity adjusters, such as sodium bicarbonate, are used to maintain proper alkalinity levels.',
    'pool_item_algaecide_title'                 => 'Algaecides',
    'pool_item_algaecide_body'                  => 'Algaecides are used to prevent or treat algae growth in the pool water. They come in different forms, including copper-based and non-metallic. Algaecides are typically used as a preventative measure or to treat existing algae growth.',
    'pool_item_clarifier_title'                 => 'Clarifiers',
    'pool_item_clarifier_body'                  => 'Clarifiers are used to improve the clarity of the pool water by causing small particles to clump together and settle to the bottom of the pool. They are often used in conjunction with a pool filter.',
    'pool_item_salt_chlorinator_title'          => 'Salt System chlorinator',
    'pool_item_salt_chlorinator_body'           => 'A salt system chlorinator is a device that uses electrolysis to convert salt into chlorine, which is then used to sanitize the pool water.',
    'pool_item_salt_chlorinator_body_2'         => 'The main function of a salt system chlorinator is to provide a convenient and effective way to sanitize the pool water without the need for traditional chlorine products. The benefits of a salt system chlorinator include: ',
    'pool_item_salt_chlorinator_function_1'     => 'Reduced need for handling and storing traditional chlorine products.',
    'pool_item_salt_chlorinator_function_2'     => 'Lower cost over time compared to traditional chlorine products.',
    'pool_item_salt_chlorinator_function_3'     => 'More consistent and stable chlorine levels, leading to better water quality and fewer fluctuations in pH levels.',
    'pool_item_salt_chlorinator_function_4'     => 'A softer and more pleasant feel to the pool water, as the salt water is gentler on skin and eyes than traditional chlorine products.',
    'pool_item_closing_1'                       => 'All these components are used to keep your pool well-maintained and running efficiently. Although it seems tedious it is always necessary to have all these items on hand, properly maintained and in perfect working condition, otherwise it may jeopardize the safety and cleanliness of your swimming pool.',
    'pool_item_closing_2'                       => 'If you have any more questions or doubts, feel free to contact our team here at Aquarius to assist you.',

